 {"id":"xf-11.3","title":"Interactive REPL Mode (xf shell)","description":"## Overview

Add `xf shell` command for interactive archive exploration. REPL with command history, tab completion, persistent session state, and query refinement. Reduces friction for exploratory searches by eliminating repeated `xf` prefix and index loading overhead.

## Background & Motivation

Power users often run many searches in sequence when exploring their archive:
```bash
xf search "meeting" --limit 5
xf search "meeting" --from 2023-01-01
xf search "meeting project" --types dm
xf list tweets --limit 10
xf stats
```

Each command:
- Re-loads the Tantivy index (50-100ms overhead)
- Requires typing full command with `xf` prefix
- Loses context from previous searches

A REPL mode solves these issues:
```
xf> search "meeting" --limit 5
... results ...
xf> refine --from 2023-01-01
... filtered results ...
xf> search "meeting project" --types dm
... results ...
xf> $1  # reference first result
... details ...
```

## UX Design

### Prompt
```
xf> _                    # Default prompt
xf [42 results]> _       # After search, show result count
xf [dm:conv-123]> _      # In DM conversation context
```

### Commands

| Command | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| search <query> [flags] | Search archive (same flags as CLI) |
| stats [--detailed] | Show archive statistics |
| list <type> [flags] | List tweets/dms/likes/etc |
| refine [flags] | Filter previous results |
| more | Show next page of results |
| show <id> or $N | Show details of result N |
| export <file> | Export current results to file |
| help [command] | Show help for command |
| quit / exit / q | Exit REPL |

### Variable Substitution

- `$1`, `$2`, etc. refer to result items by position
- `$_` refers to last selected item
- `$*` refers to all current results

### History

- Persisted to ~/.xf_history (1000 lines)
- Arrow keys for navigation
- Ctrl+R for reverse search
- History excludes quit/exit

## Technical Architecture

### New Module: src/repl.rs

```rust
use rustyline::{Editor, Config, CompletionType};
use rustyline::error::ReadlineError;

pub struct ReplState {
    storage: Storage,
    index: TantivyIndex,
    last_results: Vec<SearchResult>,
    last_query: Option<String>,
    history_path: PathBuf,
}

pub fn run(storage: Storage, index: TantivyIndex) -> Result<()> {
    let config = Config::builder()
        .history_ignore_space(true)
        .completion_type(CompletionType::List)
        .build();

    let mut rl = Editor::<ReplCompleter>::with_config(config)?;
    let mut state = ReplState::new(storage, index);

    // Load history
    let _ = rl.load_history(&state.history_path);

    loop {
        let prompt = state.format_prompt();
        match rl.readline(&prompt) {
            Ok(line) => {
                rl.add_history_entry(&line);
                match parse_and_execute(&mut state, &line) {
                    Ok(ShouldContinue::Yes) => continue,
                    Ok(ShouldContinue::Exit) => break,
                    Err(e) => eprintln!("Error: {e}"),
                }
            }
            Err(ReadlineError::Interrupted) => continue,
            Err(ReadlineError::Eof) => break,
            Err(e) => return Err(e.into()),
        }
    }

    rl.save_history(&state.history_path)?;
    Ok(())
}
